properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 9 at 3:41PM HST until February 10 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH WIND WARNING THROUGH 6 AM TUESDAY FOR THE BIG ISLAND
SUMMITS...
...HIGH WIND WARNING FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM MONDAY FOR
HALEAKALA SUMMIT...
...WIND ADVISORY THROUGH 6 PM MONDAY FOR NIIHAU KAUAI AND OAHU...
...WIND ADVISORY FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT THROUGH 6 ON MONDAY FOR
REMAINDER OF MAUI COUNTY AND THE BIG ISLAND...

* WHAT...Northwest winds 25 to 30 mph with localized gusts over 50
mph expected.

* WHERE...Niihau.

* WHEN...Through 6 PM HST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down, and cause sporadic power
outages.
properties.instruction:
Secure loose outdoor objects that can be easily blown around by
strong winds.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST MONDAY
